biography andreas phelps has spent several years in both practical and academic spheres of the building industry as an industry consultant his work with the design construction forensic analysis of building envelope systems has given him a holistic understanding of the issues facing the long term performance of building envelope systems he has also been involved with several committees focused on developing sustainability standards related to roofing systems he received his doctorate in architectural engineering from the pennsylvania state university in 2008 for his research regarding understanding the structure and moderators influencing information flow on complex health care construction projects while at penn state he also developed senior and graduate level courses related to building science and construction methods dr phelps is currently a senior staff engineer in the san francisco office of simpson gumpertz and heger consulting engineers
